{
  "texts": [
    "The SAPWNet extends the U-Net configuration by incorporating an additional branch dedicated to boundary supervision to further enhance the precision of solutions.",
    "I hs = Original hyperspectral image, I rgb = Original input RGB image, λ = Scaler weight to balance loss terms, P data (l rgb, l hs) = Data distribution, P model (l rgb) = Model distribution.",
    "3.3.7.1 SRUNet The Stacked Reversed U-Shape Network (SRUNet) (Feng et al. 2022) evolves from the U-Net architecture, aiming to improve multi-scale feature extraction and utilization at different resolutions.",
    "Net integrates several key components: Shallow Feature Extraction (SFE) for initial processing, the Stacked Reversed U-shape module (SRUM) for iterative feature extraction, the Multi-Scale Backward Fusion Module (MSBFM) for combining features across scales, and the Feature Refinement Module (FRM) for final adjustments.",
    "Differing from traditional models that upscale feature maps only at the end, SRUNet's approach through SRUM allows for the capture of intricate features progressively."
  ]
}